            <fr:title text="Virtual bicategory theory">Virtual bicategory theory</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>10261</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-0055</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-0055.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Directed graph">Directed graph</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A <fr:em>directed graph</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a collection of 0-cells <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A,B,C,\ldots \in  G]]></fr:tex> together with a collection of edges <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{e}}{B}\in  G]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>10262</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-0056</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-0056.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Free category on a directed graph">Free category on a directed graph</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Construction</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-0055.xml" title="Directed graph" addr="jms-0055" type="local">directed graph</fr:link>; a <fr:em>path</fr:em> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a sequence of compatible edges <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [A_0\xrightarrow {f_0}A_1\xrightarrow {f_1}\ldots \xrightarrow {f_{n-1}}A_n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Evidently, the free category <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G^{\star }]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> has morphisms given by paths.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>10263</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-0054</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-0054.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Virtual bicategory">Virtual bicategory</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A <fr:em>virtual bicategory</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="jms-0055.xml" title="Directed graph" addr="jms-0055" type="local">directed graph</fr:link> equipped with the following additional data:</fr:p>
                <fr:ol><fr:li>for each <fr:link href="jms-0056.xml" title="Free category on a directed graph" addr="jms-0056" type="local">path</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{\Psi }}{B}\in \mathcal {K}^{\star }]]></fr:tex> and each edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{f}}{B}\in \mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex>, a collection of 2-cells <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Psi }\xrightarrow {{\alpha }}{f}\in \mathcal {K}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>for any edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{f}}{B}]]></fr:tex>, an <fr:em>identity 2-cell</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{{\mathopen {}\left  [f\right  ]\mathclose {}}}\xrightarrow {{1_{f}}}{f}\in \mathcal {K}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>for any sequence of compatible paths <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A_0\xrightarrow {\Psi _0}\ldots \xrightarrow {\Psi _{n-1}}A_n\in  \mathcal {K}^{\star }]]></fr:tex> and 2-cells <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Psi _i}\xrightarrow {{\alpha _i}}{f_i}\in \mathcal {K}{\mathopen {}\left (A_i,A_{i+1}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{{\mathopen {}\left  [f_i\mid  i<n\right  ]\mathclose {}}}\xrightarrow {{\beta }}{g}\in \mathcal {K}{\mathopen {}\left (A_0,A_n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, a <fr:em>composite</fr:em> 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Psi _0;\ldots ;\Psi _n}\xrightarrow {{{\mathopen {}\left  [\alpha _i\mid  i<n\right  ]\mathclose {}};\beta }}{g}]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>such that the composition of 2-cells is both associative and unital with respect to identity 2-cells.</fr:li></fr:ol>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>10264</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-0057</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-0057.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Cocartesian 2-cells in a virtual bicategory">Cocartesian 2-cells in a virtual bicategory</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-0054.xml" title="Virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0054" type="local">virtual bicategory</fr:link>; given a path <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{\Psi }}{B}\in \mathcal {K}^{\star }]]></fr:tex> and an edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{f}}{B}]]></fr:tex>, a 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Psi }\xrightarrow {{\alpha }}{f}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>cocartesian</fr:em> if any 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Phi ;\Psi ;\Xi }\xrightarrow {{\beta }}{s}]]></fr:tex> factors uniquely through <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> in the sense that there exists a unique 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Phi ;{\mathopen {}\left  [f\right  ]\mathclose {}};\Xi }\xrightarrow {{\beta \setminus \alpha }}{s}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta  = {\mathopen {}\left  [\overrightarrow {1_{\Phi _i}\ldots },\alpha ,\overrightarrow {1_{\Xi _i}\ldots }\right  ]\mathclose {}};{\mathopen {}\left (\beta \setminus \alpha \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>10265</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-0058</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-0058.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Left- and right-cocartesian 2-cells in a virtual bicategory">Left- and right-cocartesian 2-cells in a virtual bicategory</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-0054.xml" title="Virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0054" type="local">virtual bicategory</fr:link>; given a <fr:link href="jms-0056.xml" title="Free category on a directed graph" addr="jms-0056" type="local">path</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{\Psi }}{B}\in \mathcal {K}^{\star }]]></fr:tex> and an edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{f}}{B}]]></fr:tex>, a 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Psi }\xrightarrow {{\alpha }}{f}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>left-cocartesian</fr:em> if for 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Psi ;\Xi }\xrightarrow {{\beta }}{s}]]></fr:tex> factors uniquely through <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> in the sense that there exists a unique 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{{\mathopen {}\left  [f\right  ]\mathclose {}};\Psi }\xrightarrow {{\beta \setminus \alpha }}{s}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta  = {\mathopen {}\left  [\alpha ,\overrightarrow {1_{\Xi _i}\ldots }\right  ]\mathclose {}};{\mathopen {}\left (\beta \setminus \alpha \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                <fr:p>Dually, given a path <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{B}\xrightarrow {{\Psi }}{C}\in \mathcal {K}^{\star }]]></fr:tex> and an edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{B}\xrightarrow {{f}}{C}]]></fr:tex>, a 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Psi }\xrightarrow {{\alpha }}{f}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>right-cocartesian</fr:em> if for 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Phi ;\Psi }\xrightarrow {{\beta }}{s}]]></fr:tex> factors uniquely through <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> in the sense that there exists a unique 2-cell <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Phi ;{\mathopen {}\left  [f\right  ]\mathclose {}}}\xrightarrow {{\beta \setminus \alpha }}{s}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta  = {\mathopen {}\left  [\overrightarrow {1_{\Phi _i}\ldots },\alpha \right  ]\mathclose {}};{\mathopen {}\left (\beta \setminus \alpha \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                <fr:p>These definitions are due to <fr:link href="arkor-mcdermott-2023-formal.xml" title="The formal theory of relative monads" addr="arkor-mcdermott-2023-formal" type="local">Arkor and McDermott</fr:link>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>10266</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-0059</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-0059.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Composites in a virtual bicategory">Composites in a virtual bicategory</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-0054.xml" title="Virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0054" type="local">virtual bicategory</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{\Psi }}{B}\in \mathcal {K}^{\star }]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-0056.xml" title="Free category on a directed graph" addr="jms-0056" type="local">path</fr:link> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex>. Then we define:</fr:p>
                <fr:ol><fr:li>a <fr:em>composite</fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Psi ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="jms-0057.xml" title="Cocartesian 2-cells in a virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0057" type="local">cocartesian 2-cell</fr:link> with domain <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Psi ]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>a <fr:em>left half-composite</fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Psi ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="jms-0058.xml" title="Left- and right-cocartesian 2-cells in a virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0058" type="local">left-cocartesian 2-cell</fr:link> with domain <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Psi ]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>a <fr:em>right half-composite</fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Psi ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="jms-0058.xml" title="Left- and right-cocartesian 2-cells in a virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0058" type="local">right-cocartesian 2-cell</fr:link> with domain <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Psi ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>10267</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-005A</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-005A.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Bicategories are virtual bicategories with all composites">Bicategories are virtual bicategories with all composites</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Observation</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A <fr:link href="jms-000E.xml" title="Bicategory" addr="jms-000E" type="local">bicategory</fr:link> is the same thing as a <fr:link href="jms-0054.xml" title="Virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0054" type="local">virtual bicategory</fr:link> that has <fr:em>all</fr:em> <fr:link href="jms-0059.xml" title="Composites in a virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0059" type="local">composites</fr:link>, as  observed by <fr:link href="https://www.hedonisticlearning.com/posts/enriched-indexed-categories-syntactically.html" type="external">Derek Elkins</fr:link>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>I still don't know if the following are the correct definitions. One would have to check that the left-composite of a pair of maps is isomorphic to the right-composite if both exist, which sounds plausible.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>10268</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-005C</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-005C.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Thunkable and linear maps in a virtual bicategory">Thunkable and linear maps in a virtual bicategory</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-0054.xml" title="Virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0054" type="local">virtual bicategory</fr:link>; we isolate two classes of edges:</fr:p>
                <fr:ol><fr:li>an edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{f}}{B}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>thunkable</fr:em> if and only if for any edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{B}\xrightarrow {{g}}{C}]]></fr:tex> there exists a <fr:link href="jms-0059.xml" title="Composites in a virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0059" type="local">left half-composite</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{{\mathopen {}\left  [f;g\right  ]\mathclose {}}}\xrightarrow {{\lambda }}{h}]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>dually, an edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{B}\xrightarrow {{g}}{C}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>linear</fr:em> if and only if for any edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{f}}{B}]]></fr:tex> there exists a <fr:link href="jms-0059.xml" title="Composites in a virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0059" type="local">right half-composite</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{{\mathopen {}\left  [f;g\right  ]\mathclose {}}}\xrightarrow {{\rho }}{h}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>18</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>10269</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-005D</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-005D.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Polarity in a virtual bicategory">Polarity in a virtual bicategory</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-0054.xml" title="Virtual bicategory" addr="jms-0054" type="local">virtual bicategory</fr:link>; we isolate two classes of objects in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex>, by analogy with the <fr:link href="jms-004B.xml" title="Positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">case</fr:link> for <fr:link href="jms-0048.xml" title="Deductive system" addr="jms-0048" type="local">deductive systems</fr:link>:</fr:p>
                <fr:ol><fr:li>an object <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\in \mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>positive</fr:em> when every edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{B}\xrightarrow {{f}}{C}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-005C.xml" title="Thunkable and linear maps in a virtual bicategory" addr="jms-005C" type="local">linear</fr:link>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>an object <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\in \mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>negative</fr:em> when every edge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{A}\xrightarrow {{f}}{B}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-005C.xml" title="Thunkable and linear maps in a virtual bicategory" addr="jms-005C" type="local">thunkable</fr:link>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
                <fr:p>Then we say that an object is <fr:em>polarized</fr:em> when it is either positive or negative in the above sense.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" hidden-when-empty="true">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:anchor>23167</fr:anchor>
        <fr:title text="Backlinks">Backlinks</fr:title>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
